# Complaint for Breach of Purchase Agreement

Pleading template to assert breach of a real estate purchase agreement and related remedies.

## Prerequisites

1. Executed purchase agreement and any amendments  
2. Escrow instructions and related documents  
3. Correspondence and notices between parties  
4. Evidence of performance or tender of performance  
5. Proof of damages incurred  
6. Jurisdiction and venue information  
7. Party identification and entity information  
8. Desired remedies and claims  

## Output Structure / Process

Use the outline below; tailor to local rules.

| Section                         | Required Content                                                  | Inputs                              |
| -------------------------------| -----------------------------------------------------------------| ---------------------------------- |
| Caption                        | Court name, division, parties, case number, jury demand if needed| Court records, party names          |
| Intro/Preliminary Statement    | Brief overview of transaction and breach                         | Transaction facts                  |
| Jurisdiction & Venue           | Basis for jurisdiction, forum selection, choice of law, venue facts | Venue facts, contract clauses     |
| Parties                       | Names, entity types, formation states, addresses, agents         | Party documents                    |
| Factual Allegations           | Timeline; contract execution; material terms; plaintiff performance; breach; notice/cure; damages | Agreements, correspondence        |
| Cause of Action: Breach       | Contract elements; cite provisions; conditions precedent; damages | Contract terms, conditions         |
| Remedy-Specific Allegations   | Specific performance, injunctive relief, escrow, lis pendens     | Remedy details                    |
| Damages                      | Damage categories and calculation                                | Damages evidence                   |
| Prayer for Relief            | Enumerated requests                                             | Remedies sought                    |
| Verification                | Verification statement if required                               | Local rule requirements            |
| Signature Block            | Attorney or party signature details                              | Attorney info                     |
| Exhibit List                | Contracts, addenda, notices, relevant documentation             | Exhibits                         |

## Element Checklist for Breach of Contract

| Element                 | Allegations to Plead                                         | Evidence / Source                |
|-------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------|
| Valid contract          | Formation, parties, consideration, attach key terms         | Executed agreement documents    |
| Plaintiff performance   | Actions taken, escrow, satisfaction or excuse of conditions  | Receipts, emails                |
| Defendant breach        | Specific obligation breached, date, failure to perform       | Notices, written communications |
| Causation & damages     | Direct and foreseeable harm caused by breach                 | Damages calculations, invoices  |

## Damages Worksheet

| Category           | Measure                      | Amount       | Source                        |
|--------------------|------------------------------|--------------|-------------------------------|
| Benefit of bargain | Difference between contract price and market value           | [Amount]    | Appraisals, contracts          |
| Consequential      | Additional losses arising from breach                         | [Amount]    | Reports, financial records     |
| Incidental        | Costs incurred in response to breach                           | [Amount]    | Invoices, receipts             |
| Reliance          | Expenses incurred in reliance on contract                       | [Amount]    | Payment records                |

## Prayer for Relief Checklist

- [ ] Request damages as calculated and supported  
- [ ] Seek specific performance if property is unique and legal remedy inadequate  
- [ ] Include injunctive relief where applicable  
- [ ] Demand attorney's fees only if contract or statute allows  
- [ ] Request costs and interest as permitted  

## Jurisdiction and Venue Facts Checklist

- [ ] Confirm court jurisdiction and venue are proper  
- [ ] Alleged compliance with forum selection clauses if any  
- [ ] State basis for choice of law and venue facts  
- [ ] Include venue-specific pleading requirements if applicable  

## Guidelines & Compliance Notes

- Confirm local pleading standard (notice vs. fact) and adjust accordingly  
- Plead conditions precedent generally or specifically per local rules  
- Attach exhibits consistent with local requirements; redact confidential info  
- Avoid requesting attorney fees without contractual or statutory basis  
- If seeking specific performance, allege uniqueness, adequacy of remedy, readiness, and ability to perform  
- For lis pendens filings, ensure statutory compliance  
- Identify and describe property with a legal description and address  
- Use placeholders like [PLAINTIFF] and [DEFENDANT] for parties  
- Avoid settlement communications protected by evidentiary rules  
- Verify requirements for verification, notarization, or civil cover sheet and comply accordingly  
- If diversity jurisdiction is involved, allege citizenship of all members and amount in controversy
